OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDerbyshire dad appeals for 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Freturn of dead son's stolen
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fpolice helmet              
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A father is appealing for the return of
OL,6, a police helmet worn by his late son   
OL,7, after it was taken in a burglary.      
OL,9,FJeff Perks said the headwear was stolen
OL,10,Ffrom his Derbyshire art studio between 
OL,11,F30 December and 5 January.             
OL,13,FHis son Steven was killed in a         
OL,14,Fhit-and-run crash in 1998 while serving
OL,15,Fwith the Metropolitan Police.          
OL,17,FMr Perks said the helmet held          
OL,18,Fsentimental value to him and his wife  
OL,19,FCarole and he hopes whoever took it    
OL,20,Fwould have a conscience to return it.  
